summary: I recently found and hatched an Absol egg. I named her Midnight and I already really love her but I'm usually a fighting and...
question: I recently found and hatched an Absol egg. I named her Midnight and I already really love her but I'm usually a fighting and psychic type expert and have never cared for an Absol or a dark type in general. Is there any advice you can give as to how to properly raise her? How should I get her used to be other pokemon?
answer:
It sounds like you were pretty lucky that the Egg you found was an Absol, and not a different Dark-type. Absol are generally very calm and pacifistic, and most other Dark-types would probably behave aggressively towards your Psychic-type Pokémon. Also, you can probably raise her slightly more similarly to how you raise your Psychic-types than how you may expect. 

She’ll need plenty of calm mental stimulation. Most Absol love listening to music since their horns can pick up on minuscule differences in the sound waves. In addition to being lots of fun, this helps them hone their predictive abilities and make them more sensitive to motions they cannot see in battle.

In terms of introducing her to your other Pokémon, I’d be more worried about how they react to her presence than the other way around. I would give them a blanket or two that Midnight sleeps on, just so that they get used to her scent and aren’t surprised. Luckily, since Absol can learn both Psychic and Fighting-type moves, you’ll be able to train them together, so that they can associate each other as part of the team more efficiently.

-Thea
